Crowthorne Woods lie within Bramshill Forest and they are administered by the{Forestry Commission. { The forest is divided into compartments for management purposes. One area which lies between the Old Wokingham Road in the west and Grid References 862640/864650 in the east, covers 125 hectares. Most of the timber is{Scots Pine}planted first in 1927 but most recently in 1973. The timber is to be used for{pulp.}
The woodland is crossed by many footpaths used by horse-riders,walkers and joggers. A Wayfaring course has been laid out.
To the east the Crown land is also covered by Forestry Commission plantations.
